# (C) control-plane/internal/store — destructive integration tests under
# TEST_DATABASE_URL gate skip without a live Postgres. Per-test coverage
# in this package is 95.2% in CI with TEST_DATABASE_URL set; without it
# the package reports 0%. Promotion to the "OR ≥95% without allowlist"
# branch waits on E86 wiring docker-compose Postgres into the unit-test
# runner — not deferred E85 work, separate-epic infrastructure.
*/packages/control-plane/internal/store

# (C) control-plane/internal/platform/pgx — the shared pgx pool constructor.
# New() runs pgxpool.ParseConfig + NewWithConfig + Ping; the happy
# connect+ping return requires a live PostgreSQL, and the NewWithConfig
# error branch is unreachable for any DSN that ParseConfig accepts. The
# testable surface IS covered (EscapeILIKE 100%, ParseConfig-error, pool
# tuning + Ping-failure + Close) — package sits at 89.5%, the residual is
# the live-DB happy path. Reclassified from BACKFILL 2026-05-27.
*/packages/control-plane/internal/platform/pgx

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (D) OS-bound — tests need kernel APIs / system keychain / WinDivert /
#                packet capture / Wails-frontend embed.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# (D) agent/internal/platform/catrust — OS trust-store integration. Per GOOS:
# macOS `security add-trusted-cert` into the System keychain, Linux
# `update-ca-certificates`, Windows certutil. InstallCACert is a thin
# temp-file + exec shim with no business logic to assert; mutating the system
# trust store needs root + a real keychain. Reclassified from BACKFILL 2026-05-27.
*/packages/agent/internal/platform/catrust

# (D) agent/internal/platform/darwin — the macOS Network Extension platform impl.
# The OS surface (NE Unix-socket listen in Start, TLS engine load from disk,
# the NE→bridge listener, libproc ProcessInfo, flow_closed audit emit) needs a
# live NE + on-disk CA + a running bridge; covered by Skill('build-agent') +
# the NE edge soak. The SAFETY-CRITICAL fail-open decision core IS now
# unit-tested (platform_flow_darwin_test.go: handleNewFlow kill-switch /
# backpressure / handler-nil passthrough + decision mapping + flow-map track,
# handleFlowUpdateHost, LookupFlowDestination, looksLikeIPLiteral, handleNEConn
# dispatch — directly verifying the NE fail-open binding). Package sits at 36.6%
# (rest is OS wiring). Reclassified from BACKFILL 2026-05-27.
*/packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin

# (D) Agent OS-direct shims — keychain, systray. (openbrowser removed: the
